  -| diffss(s0, s3)

axiom df-eeng(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, setvar s4) {
  ‚ä¢ EEG =(s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶({ <(Base ` ndx),(EE ` s0)>, <(dist ` ndx),(s1 ‚àà(EE ` s0), s2 ‚àà(EE ` s0)‚Ü¶ sum(s3 ‚àà(1[...]s0),(((s1 ` s3)[-](s2 ` s3))[^]2)))> } ‚ãÉ { <(Itv ` ndx),(s1 ‚àà(EE ` s0), s2 ‚àà(EE ` s0)‚Ü¶ { s4 ‚àà(EE ` s0)| s4[Btwn]< s1, s2 > })>, <(LineG ` ndx),(s1 ‚àà(EE ` s0), s2 ‚àà((EE ` s0)\ { s1 })‚Ü¶ { s4 ‚àà(EE ` s0)|(s4[Btwn]< s1, s2 > ‚à® s1[Btwn]< s4, s2 > ‚à® s2[Btwn]< s1, s4 >)})> }))
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s3)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, s3)
  ‚ä£ d(s2, s3)
  ‚ä£ d(s3, s4)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s1)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s2)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s4)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, s2)

}

blocks.content: The congruence relation used in the Tarski structure for the Euclidean geometry is the same as ` Cgr ` . (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 15-Mar-2019.)
